1 olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 cucumber
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
½ tbs soy sauce
½ packet hoisin sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Finely chop garlic. Slice cucumber into thin sticks. Thinly slice onion. Grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook pork mince and onion, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the soy sauce and hoisin sauce (see ingredients) and cook until combined, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
• In a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, garlic aioli, a drizzle of vinegar and a pinch of salt.

• Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Fill tortillas with slaw, carrot, cucumber and Vietnamese-style pork. Enjoy!